Question: Describe winter season in your hometown (do not disclose the name of your hometown).
Answer:
Winter in my hometown usually consists of several snowstorms worthy of at least casual conversation.  Temperatures in the winter do get below freezing at night, and through the day several times a season as well.  However, my grandparents live in the north, and I know for a fact that we are the subjects of jokes on our panicky nature down here below the Mason-Dixon Line,